# Security Policy

Thank you for helping keep psytican-bot secure. We take vulnerability reports seriously and appreciate responsible disclosure.

## Supported Versions
- We actively maintain the latest release series. Check the `pyproject.toml` for the current package version.

## Reporting a Vulnerability
- Please report security issues privately — do NOT open a public GitHub issue.
- Preferred channels:
  - Email: genesis@psytican.com
  - GitHub: Open a private Security Advisory for this repository

When reporting, include as much of the following as possible:
- Affected version(s)
- A concise description of the issue and impact
- Steps to reproduce (PoC if available)
- Any relevant logs, stack traces, or configuration
- Your contact email for follow-up

## Response Process
- We will acknowledge receipt of reports within a few business days.
- We will investigate, provide status updates, and work to produce a fix or mitigation.
- We aim to coordinate disclosure with the reporter and release a fix before public disclosure whenever feasible.

## After Disclosure
- If a fix is released, we will publish guidance and, when appropriate, a CVE.
- Please avoid public disclosure until a fix or mitigation is available, or unless agreed otherwise.

## PGP (optional)
- If you require encrypted communication, please request our PGP key via the contact channels above.

Thank you — the maintainers
